<h1>Vowels</h1>
<p>Khoekhoe features two types of vowels, oral and nasal.  Except for /e/ and /ə/ (which is rarely used), each vowel has a corresponding nasal vowel. The vowels /i/ and /e/ are only found at the end of the root, while the other vowels don't have such restrictions.</p>
<p>Nasal vowels occur due to assimilation of the neighboring nasal consonant, which is typical of most languages with nasal vowels.  They occur as either the only vowel in a root or part of a diphthong.  One exception is the nasal /õ/, which only occurs as a diphthong with /ã/.</p>
<p>There are eleven diphthong combinations on Khoekhoe, seven oral diphthongs and four nasal diphthongs. The oral diphthongs are: /ai/, /ae/, /au/, /ao/, /oe/, /oa/, and /ui/.  The nasal diphthongs are: /aĩ/, /aũ/, /õa/, and /uĩ/, which are a combination of both nasal vowels.</p>
